Exotic Kashmir, a tourist paradise of

houseboat hotels and Mogul gardens from whose name the English made "cashmere," has become a war zone of separatism and religious enmity.
At the beginning of a trip through the city of 1 million people, he turned to the four soldiers in the jeep's rear seats and ordered: "Check your weapons.
Kaul settled into the front seat, a 9mm pistol in his right hand.
"It looks like everyone here has turned into a fundamentalist with firm belief that the day is not far off when they will become independent," a state police officer said.
